    <h1>Calendar</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The plentymarkets calendar is a fully integrated calendar module. It is located in the <strong>Start » Calendar</strong> menu of your plentymarkets system. The calendar allows you to make appointments and plan deadlines. This helps you organize your own and your employees' time and improve internal processes.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_structure_of_the_calendar">1. Structure of the calendar</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The calendar displays your appointments. In addition, it shows the appointments of any users whose calenders have been made visible to you and which you have activated in the <strong>filter</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can choose to display the <strong>Day</strong>, <strong>Week</strong> or <strong>Month</strong>. In the top left corner of the calendar, the button <strong>Today</strong> is displayed. You can switch back to displaying the current day by clicking this button at any time.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The filter shows a list of all users for which you at least have read permissions. Place a check mark to display a user’s appointments in your calendar.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_setting_a_user_as_owner">2. Setting a user as owner</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Except for the <strong><a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users">user classes</a></strong><strong>API</strong> and <strong>Variable</strong>, all classes are automatically owner of a calendar. For the <strong>Variable</strong> user class, rights need to be granted to use the calendar. No calendar is available for the user class <strong>API</strong>. The right assigned to a user can be deactivated in the <strong>Owner</strong> tab at any time.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating a user as owner:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the user.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Owner</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Calendar</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.<br>
→ The user can create and edit appointments.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once a user is owner of a calendar, the new <strong>Calendar</strong> tab will be displayed and can be configured.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_calendar_settings">3. Calendar settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to configure the calendar settings and rights.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Configuring the calendar settings:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the user.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Calendar</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pay attention to the explanations given in table 1 and carry out the settings as desired.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
