<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_displaying_and_editing_appointment_details">4.2. Displaying and editing appointment details</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Click on an appointment in order to see details about it. Click on the <strong>X</strong> in the upper right-hand corner of the <strong>Appointment details</strong> window to close the detailed information. You can edit all of the details for an existing appointment. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing an appointment:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Click on the appointment that you would like to edit.<br>
→ The appointment details will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Make the desired changes.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>save icon</strong> to save the changes.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_deleting_an_appointment">4.3. Deleting an appointment</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There is also a delete function available in the appointment details. Proceed as described below to delete an appointment.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting an appointment:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Click on the appointment that you would like to delete.<br>
→ The appointment details will be displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>delete icon</strong>.<br>
→ The appointment will be deleted.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_synchronizing_the_calendar_with_external_calendar_tools">5. Synchronizing the calendar with external calendar tools</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can use a <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/CalDAV" target="_blank"><strong>CalDAV</strong></a> interface to synchronize your calendar with external calendar tools. For example, you can synchronize your calendar with tools such as Mac Calendar or iPad Calendar. The <strong>Calendar</strong> function needs to be activated in the user’s profile as described above. This is done in the <strong>Owner</strong> tab. You need to know the settings for the user in order to carry out the configuration. The settings are saved in the user’s <strong>Calendar</strong> tab. Refer to the external tool’s documentation to find out how to synchronize your calendar with it.</p>
</div>
</div>
